41. How can you use regular expressions to extract all email addresses from a given string using an array in PHP?
<?php
$text = "Contact us at admin@example.com, support@test.org, or sales@shop.net.";
preg_match_all("/[a-zA-Z0-9._%+-]+@[a-zA-Z0-9.-]+\.[a-z]{2,}/", $text, $emails);
print_r($emails[0]); // contains all matched emails
?>
Output:
Array
(
    [0] => admin@example.com
    [1] => support@test.org
    [2] => sales@shop.net
)
